<h2>
</h2>
<ul>
<li><b>The lattice dimension of a graph.</b><br>
D. Eppstein.<br>
<a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/cs.DS/0402028">arXiv:cs.DS/0402028</a>.<br>
<a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.ejc.2004.05.001"><i>Eur. J. Combinatorics</i> 26(6):585-592, 2005</a>.
<p>
Describes a polynomial time algorithm for isometrically embedding graphs
into an integer lattice of the smallest
possible dimension.  The technique involves
<a href="graph-match.html">maximum matching</a>
in an auxiliary graph derived from a
<a href="graph-cube.html">partial cube</a> representation of the input.
<p>
(<a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~eppstein/bibs/eppstein.html#The lattice dimension of a graph">BibTeX</a> --
<a href="http://fano.ics.uci.edu/cites/Document/The-lattice-dimension-of-a-graph.html">Citations</a>)
<p>
</ul>

